TECH STACK & ARCHITECTURE RULES
1. Next.js & React 19:
App Router First: Use the Next.js App Router (app/ directory). Utilize layouts, error boundaries, and loading states effectively.  
Server by Default: Default to React Server Components (RSC). Only use 'use client' when absolutely necessary (e.g., hooks, event listeners).
Data Fetching: Leverage Next.js native fetch with caching and revalidation strategies. Use Server Actions for mutations.
React 19 Standard: Use modern React 19 patterns. Do not use forwardRef; use standard ref as a prop where applicable.
2. TypeScript:
Strict Typing: Everything must be strictly typed. Avoid any. Use unknown if necessary and narrow the type.
Interfaces vs. Types: Use interface for object shapes and type for unions/intersections.
