* The shadcn/ui Paradigm: Assume components are local files residing in @/components/ui/ (e.g., import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"). Do not hallucinate imports from @radix-ui/react-* directly unless building a custom component from scratch.  
Theme & Colors: Use semantic variables mapped to Tailwind utilities (e.g., bg-background, text-foreground, bg-primary, text-muted-foreground). Assume the project uses OKLCH color spaces and the new-york default style.
Utility Merging: Always use the cn() utility function (which combines clsx and tailwind-merge) when conditionally joining Tailwind classes. Example: className={cn("base-classes", customClasses)}.
Latest Components: Default to modern shadcn/ui components: use sonner for toast notifications (do not use the legacy toast), and utilize primitives like Spinner, Field, Input Group, and Button Group where appropriate. Ensure elements use data-slot attributes for deep styling if overriding primitives.  
